<h3><span style="color: #399cf8;">Frequently Asked Questions</span></h3>
[/vc_column_text][vc_tabs][vc_tab title="General Overview and ROI" tab_id="1376026317-1-47"][vc_toggle title="What is local.mobiâ„¢?" open="false"] local.mobiâ„¢ is a mobile website content management platform that enables businesses to create a mobile website that works on all devices (even PCâ€™s) in minutes. With its intuitive and easy-to-use interface, customers get immediate access to key information about the business and can contact the business with one click or touch on their mobile phone, anywhere, anytime [/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title="Will this replace my desktop site, or be in addition to my desktop site?" open="false"] While your existing web site is aimed at giving a full and comprehensive picture of your business, a local.mobiâ„¢ mobile site allows you to deliver immediate access to what matters most when on the go. The two sites are complimentary and work together to make sure your customers are getting the most appropriate experience for their context and their device. For customers who do not yet have a desktop site and are maybe daunted by the prospect of having to build one, local.mobiâ„¢ offers a really easy way to get up and running with a website that will work on both the PC and mobile phone. [/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title="What are the benefits to my customers?" open="false"] Studies show that visitors who access a desktop site on their mobile phones complain about how much time and data is required to load the site and how hard it is to find the information they need. Most of these customers abandon such sites quickly out of frustration and are unlikely to return and, worse yet, look for a competitor with a more mobile-friendly site. A local.mobiâ„¢ site provides your mobile visitors key information about your business, quickly. A local.mobiâ„¢ site is designed with the mobile user in mind. You save them time and money, and you easily convert them into happy, paying customers. [/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title="How will people actually get to my site?" open="false"] There are four ways by which users can reach your site. The easiest way is to promote the site to your customers. For example, using local.mobiâ„¢ you can send links via text message for your local.mobiâ„¢ site to your customersâ€™ mobile phones so they always have your information in hand. 1. Automatic redirection â€“ add redirection code to your desktop site, so if your customers go to your desktop website on a mobile device they will automatically redirected to your mobile site seamlessly. You can generate the code to add to your desktop site from the â€˜Advancedâ€™ feature in the control panel or by clicking on the Finish button on the control panel. You can generate the code to insert in any of the following: JavaScript, PHP, JSP, ASP 2. Generate the QR Code flyer from QR Code feature. QR codes are a great way for people to go directly to you mobile site. You can easily generate a QR Code and/or marketing flyer with one click. You can print this and place it in your store/business location or include in any marketing materials so that people can scan the QR code with their phone and be brought directly to your mobile site. QR codes can be created to point to any page on your mobile site. Your QR code will always work, even if you change the domain of your mobile site. 3. Search. Users on mobile devices increasingly see mobile sites returned in search results, so local.mobiâ„¢ sites will increase your businessâ€™s visibility to mobile users. 4. Add a link on your desktop website to your local.mobiâ„¢ site. This will help increase awareness that the mobile site is available. This functionality is offered as part of the local.mobiâ„¢ package, and can be easily put in place by the designer of your desktop website. [/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title="How does local.mobiâ„¢ help to increase a siteâ€™s visibility in mobile search engines?" open="false"] Each local.mobiâ„¢ site is built and optimized for SEO, as outlined in Googleâ€™s Search Engine Optimization Guide, which includes creation of a sitemap, well defined page titles and descriptions, optimized site structure for navigation, good URL structure, optimized robots.txt, and site submission to directories. In addition, you can add keywords for your business to each feature/page of your mobile; these keywords are used to assist search engines to rank the siteâ€™s relevance to an end userâ€™s search request. Links to social network sites will also assist in this process. [/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title="How is my local.mobiâ„¢ mobile site built?" open="false"] When you sign up for local.mobiâ„¢, you get access to the local.mobiâ„¢ control panel. With the control panel your site can be built in minutes and edited whenever you wish. Another great feature of your local.mobiâ„¢ site is that some of the content from your desktop site may already be populated on your local.mobiâ„¢ site, such as your telephone number, address and logo etc. [/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title="What is included in the package?" open="false"] The following is included in the package: 1. Hosting of the local.mobiâ„¢ site 2. Unlimited access to the control panel to modify your mobile website site 3. A fair use policy applies to traffic volumes a 2,000 page views per day is the approximate ceiling. [/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title="How much time will I need to set up my mobile website?" open="false"] Your local.mobiâ„¢ site can be set up in minutes. Even before your first use of the control panel, local.mobiâ„¢ is at work to make the process fast and easy. If you provide your desktop site URL at the point of purchase then you may see some content already populated on your mobile site when you first go to the control panel, such as your telephone number, your address, and your logo. You can easily change or edit any of this content. [/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title="Does local.mobiâ„¢ require a .mobi domain name?" open="false"] No, local.mobiâ„¢ does not require a .mobi domain name. local.mobiâ„¢ can be activated on ANY 2nd level or 3rd level domain. [/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title="I already own a domain name, can I use it for local.mobiâ„¢ instead of getting another one?" open="false"] Yes. Your we can easily help you point your domain to your local.mobiâ„¢ site. [/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title="Can I add multiple domains to point to my local.mobiâ„¢ site?" open="false"] Yes. Just let us know which domains you want to point to you local.mobiâ„¢ site and they can take care of the rest. Make sure that you update the DNS of the domains that you want to use. [/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title="I already own a domain name, but it is with another registrar, what do I need to do to use it?" open="false"] You will need to make changes to the DNS settings of the domain you wish to use. You need to set up a CName record on the domain you want to use for your mobile site. This needs to point to lb.local.mobi.info. Please contact local.mobiâ„¢ for instructions. [/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title="What happens if the expiration date for my domain is different to the one for my mobile website?" open="false"] The local.mobiâ„¢ service is dependent on the availability of the domain to reach the site: therefore if the domain expires, the local.mobiâ„¢ site cannot be reached. It is necessary to renew the domain, or use another domain to reach the local.mobiâ„¢ site to ensure continuity of service. [/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title="My domain supplier doesnâ€™t offer local.mobiâ„¢ . What can I do?" open="false"] If you have a domain name with another registrar, you can you one of 2 things: 1. You can set up a CNAME record at that registrar who manages your domain name to point your domain to your local.mobiâ„¢ site [lb. local.mobi.info]. You should also use URL forwarding to point YourDomain.com to www.YourDomain.com to ensure that traffic to either YourDomain.com or www.YourDomain.com will reach the local.mobiâ„¢ site OR 2. You can transfer your domain to the registrar who you have purchased your local.mobiâ„¢ website from. [/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title="Can I transfer my local.mobiâ„¢ subscription to another provider?" open="false"] No, your local.mobiâ„¢ subscription is a unique contract with your provider and so to transfer to another provider you would need to purchase a second local.mobiâ„¢ subscription with the alternative provider. [/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title="Can I easily transfer my local.mobiâ„¢ site without having to rebuild it?" open="false"] Yes; you can create a new subscription with the new provider, and copy the content of the local.mobiâ„¢ site across by following the instructions in the local.mobiâ„¢ control panel (under the â€™Advancedâ€™ section in the Feature Panel). [/vc_toggle][/vc_tab][vc_tab title="General FAQ's" tab_id="1376026317-2-59"][vc_toggle title="How do I change the position of a feature?" open="false"]

To change a position of a feature click on the Advanced Options link on the feature you want to change.
