Google Analytics has advanced options that support tracking of mobile. Follow the steps below to add your Google Analytics tracking code to your mobile website: 1. Open Google Analytics â€“ https://www.google.com/analytics/settings/home 2. Select the Account that the site is part of. 3. The next page lists the URLâ€™s being tracked. Click â€œEditâ€ on the right hand side of the row for the domain you are using for your mobile site. 4. In the top right corner of the profile table click â€œCheck Statusâ€. 5. Under â€œInstructions for adding trackingâ€, click on the â€œAdvancedâ€ tab. 6. Under â€œWhat are you tracking?â€ select â€œA site built for a mobile phoneâ€, then select â€œPHPâ€ from the radio lists. 7. In the pane â€œpaste code on your mobile siteâ€, note down the value for the line â€œ$GA_ACCOUNT = â€œMO-XXXXXX-Xâ€;â€, this is your tracking ID. e.g. MO-1231234-2 8. Click â€œSave and Finishâ€ in the bottom right hand corner of the page. 9. Open the control panel 10. Click on the â€œFeaturesâ€ tab. 11. Scroll down to â€œGoogle Analyticsâ€ and enter the tracking ID from earlier, then click OK. e.g. MO-1231234-2

